  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Standardize Pagination Controls Across All Language Versions\n\nFix pagination display inconsistencies where buttons and page information text appear differently across language versions of the application.\n\nRequirements:\n- Replace text-based pagination buttons (\"Next\", \"Previous\", etc.) with arrow icons across all language versions\n- Use → for next and ← for previous (or appropriate arrow icon set)\n- Ensure \"Page X of Y\" text is properly translated and displays correctly for all supported languages\n- Specifically fix the Polish language version where \"Page 1 of 2\" text is currently showing incorrectly\n- Verify pagination controls render consistently on all localized versions\n- Test with different page counts (single page, multiple pages, edge cases like page 1 and last page)\n- Ensure arrow buttons maintain proper disabled states (e.g., previous disabled on page 1, next disabled on last page)",
